# Kafka Messaging

## Producer Pattern
```java
@Log4j2 @Service
public class OrderEventProducer {
    private final KafkaTemplate<String, OrderEvent> kafkaTemplate;

    public void send(String topic, String key, OrderEvent event) {
        kafkaTemplate.send(topic, key, event);
        kafkaTemplate.flush();
    }
}
```
- Key is always `String`

## Consumer Pattern
```java
@KafkaListener(
    topics = "${ORDER_EVENT_TOPIC}",
    groupId = "order-processor",
    containerFactory = "avroListenerContainerFactory")
public void consume(@Header(name = KafkaHeaders.RECEIVED_KEY) String key,
                    ConsumerRecord<String, OrderEvent> record) {
    log.info("Received key=[{}]", key);
}
```
- Explicit `groupId` and `containerFactory` on every listener
- Extract key via `@Header(name = KafkaHeaders.RECEIVED_KEY)`

## Error Handling
- `DefaultErrorHandler` with exponential backoff
- `ErrorHandlingDeserializer` wraps all consumers
- Failed records sent to DLQ after exhausting retries

## Avro Schema Conventions
- Format: Avro IDL (`.avdl`) in `src/main/resources/avro/`
- PascalCase records, camelCase fields
- `@doc` annotations for documentation
- Evolution: add optional fields with defaults, never remove/rename
- Confluent Schema Registry with TopicNameStrategy
